.TH REQPKGS "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
reqpkgs \- Install required packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B reqpkgs
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE_LIST\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B reqpkgs
is a script for installing required packages from a list or file. It automatically detects the package manager and installs the specified packages.
.PP
The script supports multiple package managers and can install packages from requirements files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B reqpkgs requirements.txt
Install packages from requirements file
.TP
.B reqpkgs package1 package2
Install specified packages
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/reqpkgs/settings.conf
User configuration file for reqpkgs preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Package manager not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Automatically detects system package manager
.IP \(bu 2
Supports apt, dnf, pacman, and more
.IP \(bu 2
Can read from requirements files
